Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now JOHANNESBURG – President Cyril Ramaphosa will lead Freedom Day celebrations in Bloemfontein on Friday. The country held its first democratic election on this day in 1994. Freedom Day: A milestone in SA's history Since then, the day and month are used to mark the country's liberation. President Cyril Ramaphosa will on Friday lead the national Freedom Day celebrations to be held at the Dr Rantli Molemela Stadium in Bloemfontein, Free State. https://t.co/uf2WKkciAs This year's celebrations recognise the roles Nelson Mandela and Albertina Sisulu played in the struggle for freedom. The government says freedom can only be realised through radical socio-economic transformation. The Presidency said the president would use Freedom Day to ensure the legacy of struggle veterans live on. eNCA